### 1.2 How theming and density work

Tokens are scoped by `data-*` attributes on an ancestor element (typically `<html>` or `<body>` or the app root):

```html
<html data-gamma-theme="light" data-gamma-density="comfortable">
```

- **Theme** attribute selects color tokens: `dark`, `light`, `dark-classic`, `dark-hc`, `light-hc`.
- **Density** attribute selects sizing/typography tokens: `compact`, `regular`, `comfortable`, `spacious`.
- Each density file redefines the same token names with different values (e.g. `--gamma-typography-title-font-size` is `16px` in compact, `20px` in comfortable). **Therefore: never copy a tokenŌĆÖs resolved value into component CSS ŌĆö always reference the variable** so density switching keeps working.

