## 2. Migration rules

### 2.1 Typography

1. Remove all custom `@font-face` declarations for Effra or any other brand font from app CSS ŌĆö the design system already ships them. If app CSS loads its own font files, delete those rules and verify `index.css` of the design system is imported once at app entry.
1. Map every text style to the closest Gamma role using this heuristic (confirm against actual density values):
- Page hero / largest heading ŌåÆ `supersize`
- Page heading (h1) ŌåÆ `display`
- Section heading (h2/h3) / card titles ŌåÆ `title`
- Sub-headings, labels-with-emphasis ŌåÆ `subtitle`
- Default paragraph text ŌåÆ `body` (or `body-sm` for dense tables/secondary text)
- Helper text, timestamps, footnotes ŌåÆ `caption`
1. Replace each mapped ruleŌĆÖs `font-family`, `font-size`, `line-height`, `font-weight` with the full token set of one role ŌĆö do not mix roles (e.g. title font-size with caption line-height).
1. Replace `font-weight: 600/700` with `var(--gamma-font-weight-bold)` and `font-weight: 400` with `var(--gamma-font-weight-regular)`. Buttons use `--gamma-font-weight-button`. Note GammaŌĆÖs ŌĆ£boldŌĆØ is 500 ŌĆö flag anywhere this visibly changes hierarchy.

### 2.2 Borders and radii

- Map border widths: `1px ŌåÆ thin`, `2px ŌåÆ medium`, `3px+ ŌåÆ thick`.
- Map radii to the nearest token: `0 ŌåÆ none`, `1ŌĆō2px ŌåÆ subtle`, `3ŌĆō5px ŌåÆ medium`, `6ŌĆō10px ŌåÆ rounded`, pills/circles (`50%`, large px) ŌåÆ `circle`.
- Mapping must be by nearest token, never exact-match-or-skip. Record every approximation in the report (┬¦6).

### 2.3 Colors

- Inventory all hardcoded colors (hex, rgb/rgba, hsl, named) in the provided CSS.
- Map each to the semantically correct Gamma color token from the theme files (e.g. surface/background, text-primary/secondary, border, interactive/primary, success/warning/error) ŌĆö match by **role**, not by closest hex value, so dark and HC themes work automatically.
- Never reference a theme-specific value directly; only `var(--gamma-...)`.
- If a color has no reasonable semantic token, flag it instead of guessing.

### 2.4 Icons

- Replace custom icon fonts, inline SVG icons used for standard glyphs, and icon-sizing CSS with `.gamma-icon` (+ `.sm` / `.lg`) and Material Symbols Outlined ligatures where feasible.
- Where a bespoke SVG must stay (logos, custom illustrations), size it with icon typography tokens rather than hardcoded px.

### 2.5 Density-awareness

- Any padding/margin/gap that visually tracks text size should use tokens (spacing tokens if they exist in the package; otherwise `em` relative to the tokenized font-size) so compact/spacious modes scale correctly.
- Do not hardcode component heights that would break under a different density (e.g. a 32px input that overflows in spacious mode). Prefer `min-height` driven by line-height + padding tokens.

